Notebook[{
Cell["\<\
The \[Zeta](7) cellular family: the q_n operator \[LongDash] definitions and \
validation\
\>", "Title",ExpressionUUID->"345f6114-ec35-46db-9d7a-c20449cbd9b1"],

Cell["\<\
Totally symmetric M_{0,10} Brown\[Dash]Zudilin cellular integral, permutation \
(10,2,4,1,6,3,8,5,9,7). q_n is the leading (\[Zeta](7)-slot) coefficient \
sequence, computable by the McCarthy\[Dash]Osburn\[Dash]Straub diagonal \
construction (arXiv:1705.05586 \[Section]3.2); anchors q_0, q_1, q_2 = 1, 61, \
52921 match the printed values in Brown\[Dash]Zudilin. The order-4, degree-19 \
operator below was reconstructed 2026-07-17 from 105 exact terms \
(low-coupling-window dynamic programming, 3-prime CRT ~2^125, exact-relation \
completion of the large coefficients) and is CERTIFIED in the finite sense: \
it annihilates all 74 stored exact terms at every admissible offset. It is \
NOT yet proven for all n (a creative-telescoping certificate is the pending \
route). Notebook assembled 2026-07-19; data embedded, fully self-contained.\
\>", "Text",ExpressionUUID->"b1e6831f-9957-4fec-868d-c94ba9d19711"],

Cell["1. Exact data", "Section",ExpressionUUID->"ed29fbaa-5cb2-4746-a4a7-b963a4109291"],

