Cell["2. The operator", "Section",ExpressionUUID->"404ea7e0-11be-4f53-bd1c-e1863b382629"],

Cell["\<\
(* c_k(n): Horner evaluation of the degree-19 coefficient polynomial. (Not \
Sum[...n^i...]: Mathematica's 0^0 is Indeterminate, which would silently \
break the n = 0 offset.) *)
c[k_, n_] := Fold[#1 n + #2 &, 0, Reverse[Cpoly[[k + 1]]]]
L[f_, n_] := Sum[c[k, n] f[n + k], {k, 0, 4}]  (* the recurrence: L[q, n] = 0 \
*)\
\>", "Input",ExpressionUUID->"79eb7303-f3ba-4008-89c5-5c6482feb677"],

Cell["\<\
3. Validation 1 \[LongDash] the operator annihilates all 74 exact terms \
(expect {70, {}})\
\>", "Section",ExpressionUUID->"646557d0-4532-4f33-a7e6-cb56111c028d"],

Cell["\<\
q[n_] := qTerms[[n + 1]];
offsets = Range[0, Length[qTerms] - 5];
{Length[offsets], Select[offsets, L[q, #] =!= 0 &]}\
\>", "Input",ExpressionUUID->"63e688b7-b04d-4bd0-b934-8e65e2f66386"],

Cell["\<\
4. Validation 2 \[LongDash] characteristic polynomial and its Q(Sqrt[3]) \
sector factorization (expect True, True)\
\>", "Section",ExpressionUUID->"657a2534-3a85-491c-9d4c-3ed7fb5bf380"],

Cell["\<\
lead = Table[Cpoly[[k + 1, -1]], {k, 0, 4}];
charPoly = \[Lambda]^4 - 6340 \[Lambda]^3 + 67974 \[Lambda]^2 - 6340 \
\[Lambda] + 1;
lead/(GCD @@ lead) === CoefficientList[charPoly, \[Lambda]]\
\>", "Input",ExpressionUUID->"0bd4349b-5e5b-40c1-b81b-7bdf2ed17bbf"],

Cell["\<\
a = 3170 + 1824 Sqrt[3]; b = 3170 - 1824 Sqrt[3];
Expand[(\[Lambda]^2 - a \[Lambda] + 1) (\[Lambda]^2 - b \[Lambda] + 1)] === \
charPoly\
\>", "Input",ExpressionUUID->"a820d403-9369-49ca-a29d-92dbea6d78ea"],

Cell["5. Sectors and the irrationality threshold", "Section",ExpressionUUID->"3da5815d-8cf1-4e20-9928-8abe2a942657"],

Cell["\<\
The char poly is palindromic; over Q(Sqrt[3]) it splits into sector A (roots \
\[Lambda]_max \[TildeTilde] 6329.26 and its reciprocal 1.58*10^-4) and sector \
B (10.645 and 0.0939). For a weight-7 form with d_n^7 denominators the decay \
must beat Exp[-7] \[TildeTilde] 9.12*10^-4: sector A passes with margin Log[\
\[Lambda]_max] - 7 \[TildeTilde] 1.7529; sector B fails by two orders of \
magnitude. (Which sector the primitive form I\[Prime] rides is a separate, \
evidence-grade analysis \[LongDash] see worthiness/ZETA7_RESIDUE_I3.md: the \
answer is sector B, so the symmetric family cannot reach the pairwise \
irrationality theorem.)\
\>", "Text",ExpressionUUID->"81ffff49-1166-4d7d-88f0-af8d12fd90e1"],

Cell["\<\
sectorA = Sort[\[Lambda] /. NSolve[\[Lambda]^2 - a \[Lambda] + 1 == 0, \
\[Lambda], WorkingPrecision -> 30]];
sectorB = Sort[\[Lambda] /. NSolve[\[Lambda]^2 - b \[Lambda] + 1 == 0, \
\[Lambda], WorkingPrecision -> 30]];
{sectorA, sectorB}\
\>", "Input",ExpressionUUID->"efd0e5aa-e24b-4a01-b711-4983e2326c97"],

Cell["\<\
(* threshold tests: a sector passes iff Exp[7]*smallRoot < 1 *)
{N[Log[Max[sectorA]] - 7, 10], N[Exp[7] Min[sectorA], 5], N[Exp[7] \
Min[sectorB], 5]}\
\>", "Input",ExpressionUUID->"3dcb7d7a-a509-4aa5-baf5-18b606e851f6"],

Cell["6. Convergence sanity", "Section",ExpressionUUID->"6a85c6af-3b08-4de1-835e-ade23818d793"],

Cell["\<\
(* the term ratio approaches \[Lambda]_max \[TildeTilde] 6329.26 (still ~6032 \
at n = 73: subexponential factors) *)
N[qTerms[[-1]]/qTerms[[-2]], 10]\
\>", "Input",ExpressionUUID->"cf96617b-c351-4558-b93c-b0870150f675"],

Cell["7. Scope", "Section",ExpressionUUID->"f2b2ac9e-da99-46a0-a8f4-986064a6acae"],

Cell["\<\
Established here: a finite certificate \[LongDash] the displayed operator \
annihilates all 74 exact q_n, its leading characteristic polynomial is \
exactly \[Lambda]^4 - 6340\[Lambda]^3 + 67974\[Lambda]^2 - 6340\[Lambda] + 1, \
and the Q(Sqrt[3]) sector splitting is an exact identity. NOT established \
here: that the operator annihilates q_n for ALL n (pending a \
creative-telescoping certificate; see worthiness/ZETA7_CT_CERTIFICATE.md), \
and anything about the primitive ladder I\[Prime] (see \
worthiness/ZETA7_RESIDUE_I3.md and worthiness/ZETA7_DWORK_FROM_SOL.txt \
\[Section]T2 for why a telescoper for the full integral does not \
automatically govern the coefficient ladders). To verify: Evaluation \
\[RightPointer] Evaluate Notebook; Section 3 must return {70, {}} and Section \
4 must return True twice.\
